caption: BEWARE of the blonde lady at the register, she tries to add extra charges to your tab. I've caught her doing this twice now and questioned her about it! The only only reason why I can't give 0 stars is because this rating system won't allow me.  The cooks usually have scowls on their faces when they're preparing your food.  I specifically told the cook that I ONLY wanted scrambled eggs, but I had to fill out their form.  There was no place on the form to just order scrambled eggs, so I filled it out as thoroughly as I could, but put in the notes section, "Just Scrambled eggs" (see attached photo).  They charged me $9 for scrambled eggs - it wasn't even an omelet!  (see attached receipt)  The eggs were slightly burnt, too.  Poor customer service and poor management. Of course, they'll respond with something like "we explained that to you" or "we gave you extra scrambled eggs" or some other lame excuse.  What they didn't explain was why they never charged me $9 before when I came in to get scrambled eggs (I think it was around $4 or $5).  Magically, the price doubled for no reason.  WILL NEVER COME HERE AGAIN!!!!!!!!

The Brown Bag is a well designed (if you love a wood theme) breakfast/lunch spot in downtown DC. It's just north of Franklin Square and opens early to serve the breakfast crowd. They brew drip coffee, bake pastries (the mocha muffin is excellent), and make breakfast sandwiches to order.  A few hours later, it flips to lunch making sandwiches, salads, etc. The space is large and can accommodate large groups.  If you want a fast breakfast/lunch experience in a more well designed spot, head to Brown Bag.

I had their peanut noodles, and 3/4 through my lunch I noticed little bugs. They were definitely bugs because my friend and I looked at them closely and they had legs. They were very, very tiny. We found a total of about 5 before we decided we definitely had to tell the manager. They gave me my money back. Not sure if they were from the veggies (broccoli), hygiene issues, or anything else. But I am sure not to go back there. I think they should inspect their ingredients carefully if that is the case.
